    "what_description": "Erythrocephalum foliosum is a species of plant in the family Asteraceae. It is a perennial herb with a woody base, growing up to 1.5 meters tall, and has linear to lance-shaped leaves that are 5-20 centimeters long and 0.5-2 centimeters wide. The leaves are arranged oppositely on the stem, and the plant produces a solitary capitulum at the apex, which is 5-10 centimeters in diameter, with yellowish to reddish-brown florets. The florets have a tubular corolla and five lobed ray florets, with the disc florets being hermaphroditic and the ray florets being female. It is native to tropical Africa and is commonly found in woodland and grassland areas.",
