    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Erythrocephalum foliosum are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial. The anti-inflammatory property of Erythrocephalum foliosum is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which have been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The antioxidant property is associated with the saponins present in the plant, which scavenge free radicals and protect cells from oxidative damage. Additionally, the antimicrobial property of Erythrocephalum foliosum is due to the volatile oils, which exhibit broad-spectrum antibacterial and antifungal activities, thereby preventing infections and promoting wound healing. The immunomodulatory effect of Erythrocephalum foliosum is also significant, as it enhances the host's immune response against pathogens and reduces the risk of diseases.",
