    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Erythrocephalum foliosum are sesquiterpene lactones including erinaceae and foliosin, flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol, phenolic acids like ferulic acid and vanillic acid, as well as diterpenes and alkaloids. These constituents have been found to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant and antimicrobial properties. Erinaceae has been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory activity through inhibition of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Quercetin has been found to have antioxidant properties, scavenging free radicals and reducing oxidative stress. Foliosin has been reported to possess antimicrobial activity, inhibiting the growth of certain microorganisms.",
