    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Erythrocephalum foliosum are infusion, made by steeping the leaves in boiling water, tea, a more concentrated infusion, decoction, a preparation where the leaves are boiled in water for a longer period, and tincture, a concentrated liquid extract obtained through solvent extraction. These preparations are used to treat various ailments, including fever and infections, due to the plant's antipyretic and antimicrobial properties. A salve can also be prepared from the leaves, used topically to treat skin conditions and wounds. The preparation method for these herbal remedies is often based on traditional knowledge and can be modified to suit individual needs. These preparations can be used individually or in combination to enhance their therapeutic effects, but their efficacy and safety should be verified through scientific studies.",
