    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Erythrocephalum foliosum improperly include experience nausea, cause diarrhea, induce nausea, induce vomiting, and develop allergic reaction. These adverse effects can occur due to the plant's toxic compounds, particularly sesquiterpene lactones, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation and inflammation. Improper use may lead to overexposure to these compounds, resulting in symptoms such as stomach cramps, dizziness, and skin rashes. Allergic reactions may manifest as hives, itching, and difficulty breathing, requiring immediate medical attention. In severe cases, improper use of Erythrocephalum foliosum can lead to anaphylaxis, a life-threatening condition that necessitates emergency care.",
